title: Reboot behavior
order: 30
required: true
selection: one
default: reboot
description: Chooses what the machine does after installation finishes.
applies_to:
  os:
    - rhel7
    - rhel8
    - rhel9
    - rhel10
  profiles:
    - minimal
    - small_disk
    - developer_workstation
options:
  - id: reboot
    file: reboot.ks.j2
    title: Reboot after install
    description: Reboots the machine automatically after installation completes.
    recommended: true
    risk: low
    warning: Make sure PXE boot order will not reinstall the machine in a loop.
    requires: []
    conflicts:
      - shutdown
  - id: shutdown
    file: shutdown.ks.j2
    title: Shut down after install
    description: Shuts the machine down after installation completes.
    recommended: false
    risk: low
    warning: Useful for golden tests or staged installs, but not ideal when post-install automation expects the machine to come online.
    requires: []
    conflicts:
      - reboot
notes: Reboot is the better default for PXE workflows that continue into Ansible or other post-install automation.
tags:
  - required
  - installer
  - default

